						               													<description>The dealer shuffles the orange stuff-cards and spreads them all face down. Place the blue stuff-cards face down in a deck to the side of Madame Blueberry's pile of orange cards. The youngest player starts.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player draws a card from the orange pile and places it face up in front of him/her.&amp;#10;If a Thankful card with a heart is drawn, discard all of your stuff cards and the next player goes.&amp;#10;When an orange stuff card is drawn, put it in front of you. Even if it's a card you don't need.&amp;#10;If a salesman card is drawn with a $ sign, the player must draw 2 blue stuff cards. Place those stuff cards in front of you and discard the salesman card.&amp;#10;If the Madame Blueberry card is drawn, keep on drawing until you get a Thankful card. Put back all the other stuff cards, including the ones you already had.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player who gets four thankful cards to make a happy heart wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
